(window.webpackJsonp=window.webpackJsonp||[]).push([[38],{297:function(module,exports){module.exports={compilerOutput:[],storyContent:{inkVersion:19,root:[[{"->t->":"chapter_12_halo_of_flies_start"},{"->t->":"yield"},{"->t->":"chapter_12_halo_of_flies_directives_received"},{"->t->":"yield"},{"->t->":"chapter_12_halo_of_flies_end_of_show"},{"->t->":"yield"},{"->t->":"chapter_12_halo_of_flies_encore"},"ev","str","^","/str","/ev",{"->":"done"},["done",{"#f":5,"#n":"g-0"}],null],"done",{chapter_12_halo_of_flies_start:[['^<play-sound group="music" name="boardroom-daydream" />',"\n",'^<play-sound group="music" name="raw-bit-processor" />',"\n","^<h5><time>2301.06.14:1730</time></h5>","\n","^<p>","\n","^Evening. The sun just beginning to creep under the horizon. All the smog is bright as the sun stares us down, straight on.","\n","^</p>","\n",{"->t->":"yield"},"^<p>","\n","^The Palace is alive, though. Eight bands, one night, four hours of extreme noise played by mad anarcho-punks. We're <em>very</em> fashionably late, and the openers are already done. Show probably opened late, too.","\n","^</p>","\n","^<p>","\n","^The flier is stuck to all the walls outside, and in the lobby.","\n","^</p>","\n","^<ul>","\n","^<li>Tiger Actual</li>","\n","^<li>Hollywood Baphomets </li>","\n","^<li>Baronette Mantissa</li>","\n","^<li>Violence Kings</li>","\n","^<li>ADAM Contingent</li>","\n","^<li>FUBAR</li>","\n","^<li>The People's Revolutionary Society of Noise</li>","\n","^<li>Interrupt Signal</li>","\n","^</ul>","\n","^<p>","\n","^The warehouse has three stages, one primary, two secondary.","\n","^</p>","\n",{"->t->":"yield"},'^<stop-sound group="music" name="boardroom-daydream" />',"\n",'^<update-sound group="music" name="raw-bit-processor" volume="0.35" />',"\n","^<p>","\n","^Tiger Actual, FUBAR, and the PRSN are playing the primary stage.","\n","^</p>","\n","^<p>","\n","^The Violence Kings, ADAM Contingent (less its recent frontman, suspected on the matrix of liking young girls a bit too much; they executed his termination in classic punk style), and Baron Mantissa are on one secondary stage.","\n","^</p>","\n","^<p>","\n","^Hollywood Baphomets and Interrupt Signal are on the other.","\n","^</p>","\n",{"->t->":"yield"},"^<p>","\n","^The crowd is beginning to pack in. All colors and genders, sovereign in the postdiluvian night, mostly very young. They have fierce eyes and impossibly wide smiles, laughs barking in the dark structure now growing opaque through smoke machines and vaporized psychoactives.","\n","^</p>","\n","^<p>","\n","^I am in the corner, watching the headcount grow. Lystra and Lefteris are off scoping the exits. I'm catching the tunes, and they'll go to whichever stages I don't.","\n","^</p>","\n","^<p>","\n","^A carbine is digging into my ribs under an elaborate and skinless anarcho-death getup. The rest of the operating group is in similar vestments, scattered near the exits and hallways.","\n","^</p>","\n","^<p>","\n","^A punk girl needs a hardcore name, of course.","\n","^</p>","\n",["ev",{"^->":"chapter_12_halo_of_flies_start.0.99.$r1"},{"temp=":"$r"},"str",{"->":".^.s"},[{"#n":"$r1"}],"/str","/ev",{"*":".^.^.c-0",flg:18},{s:['^Andrea "Methedrine" Eldridge.',{"->":"$r",var:!0},null]}],["ev",{"^->":"chapter_12_halo_of_flies_start.0.100.$r1"},{"temp=":"$r"},"str",{"->":".^.s"},[{"#n":"$r1"}],"/str","/ev",{"*":".^.^.c-1",flg:18},{s:["^Justina Putrescence.",{"->":"$r",var:!0},null]}],["ev",{"^->":"chapter_12_halo_of_flies_start.0.101.$r1"},{"temp=":"$r"},"str",{"->":".^.s"},[{"#n":"$r1"}],"/str","/ev",{"*":".^.^.c-2",flg:18},{s:["^Plural Melanie And Their Scumfucs.",{"->":"$r",var:!0},null]}],{"c-0":["ev",{"^->":"chapter_12_halo_of_flies_start.0.c-0.$r2"},"/ev",{"temp=":"$r"},{"->":".^.^.99.s"},[{"#n":"$r2"}],"\n","ev","str",'^Andrea "Methedrine" Eldridge',"/str","/ev",{"VAR=":"chapter_12_halo_of_flies_name_choice",re:!0},{"->":".^.^.g-0"},{"#f":5}],"c-1":["ev",{"^->":"chapter_12_halo_of_flies_start.0.c-1.$r2"},"/ev",{"temp=":"$r"},{"->":".^.^.100.s"},[{"#n":"$r2"}],"\n","ev","str","^Justina Putrescence","/str","/ev",{"VAR=":"chapter_12_halo_of_flies_name_choice",re:!0},{"->":".^.^.g-0"},{"#f":5}],"c-2":["ev",{"^->":"chapter_12_halo_of_flies_start.0.c-2.$r2"},"/ev",{"temp=":"$r"},{"->":".^.^.101.s"},[{"#n":"$r2"}],"\n","ev","str","^Plural Melanie And Their Scumfucs","/str","/ev",{"VAR=":"chapter_12_halo_of_flies_name_choice",re:!0},{"->":".^.^.g-0"},{"#f":5}],"g-0":["^<p>","\n","^Hardest name in the entire damn Palace. Nobody fucks with ","<>",["ev",{"CNT?":".^.^.^.c-0"},"/ev",{"->":".^.b",c:!0},{b:["\n","^Methedrine Eldridge.","\n",{"->":".^.^.^.7"},null]}],["ev",{"CNT?":".^.^.^.c-1"},"/ev",{"->":".^.b",c:!0},{b:["\n","^Justina Putrescence.","\n",{"->":".^.^.^.7"},null]}],[{"->":".^.b"},{b:["\n","<>","^Plural Melanie. Or their innumerably vicious Scumfucs.","\n",{"->":".^.^.^.7"},null]}],"nop","\n","^</p>","\n",["ev",{"^->":"chapter_12_halo_of_flies_start.0.g-0.11.$r1"},{"temp=":"$r"},"str",{"->":".^.s"},[{"#n":"$r1"}],"/str","/ev",{"*":".^.^.c-3",flg:18},{s:["^I move to the primary stage.",{"->":"$r",var:!0},null]}],["ev",{"^->":"chapter_12_halo_of_flies_start.0.g-0.12.$r1"},{"temp=":"$r"},"str",{"->":".^.s"},[{"#n":"$r1"}],"/str","/ev",{"*":".^.^.c-4",flg:18},{s:["^I'll watch the secondary stage.",{"->":"$r",var:!0},null]}],["ev",{"^->":"chapter_12_halo_of_flies_start.0.g-0.13.$r1"},{"temp=":"$r"},"str",{"->":".^.s"},[{"#n":"$r1"}],"/str","/ev",{"*":".^.^.c-5",flg:18},{s:["^I'm going to the tertiary stage.",{"->":"$r",var:!0},null]}],{"c-3":["ev",{"^->":"chapter_12_halo_of_flies_start.0.g-0.c-3.$r2"},"/ev",{"temp=":"$r"},{"->":".^.^.11.s"},[{"#n":"$r2"}],"\n","ev","str","^tiger","/str","/ev",{"VAR=":"chapter_12_halo_of_flies_band_choice",re:!0},{"->t->":"chapter_12_halo_of_flies_primary_stage"},{"->":".^.^.^.g-1"},{"#f":5}],"c-4":["ev",{"^->":"chapter_12_halo_of_flies_start.0.g-0.c-4.$r2"},"/ev",{"temp=":"$r"},{"->":".^.^.12.s"},[{"#n":"$r2"}],"\n","ev","str","^mantissa","/str","/ev",{"VAR=":"chapter_12_halo_of_flies_band_choice",re:!0},{"->t->":"chapter_12_halo_of_flies_secondary_stage"},{"->":".^.^.^.g-1"},{"#f":5}],"c-5":["ev",{"^->":"chapter_12_halo_of_flies_start.0.g-0.c-5.$r2"},"/ev",{"temp=":"$r"},{"->":".^.^.13.s"},[{"#n":"$r2"}],"\n","ev","str","^baphomet","/str","/ev",{"VAR=":"chapter_12_halo_of_flies_band_choice",re:!0},{"->t->":"chapter_12_halo_of_flies_tertiary_stage"},{"->":".^.^.^.g-1"},{"#f":5}],"#f":5}],"g-1":["ev","void","/ev","->->",{"#f":5}]}],{"#f":1}],chapter_12_halo_of_flies_primary_stage:["^<p>","\n","^Tiger Actual is opening. A few kids in a cluster to my right are looking the band up on their devices and sharing what they find. Two women. Sister Cat and Rabies Sonderlust. Synthesizers. Noise. Dancing.","\n","^</p>","\n",{"->t->":"yield"},'^<stop-sound group="music" name="raw-bit-processor" />',"\n",'^<play-sound group="music" name="cowardice-diegetic-right" />',"\n",'^<play-sound group="music" name="rage-diegetic-right" />',"\n",'^<play-sound group="music" name="razors-and-twigs-remix" />',"\n","^<p>","\n","^The duo steps up to the stage, guitar and synthesizer in hand, lips poised above microphones. Rabies speaks: \"This is a song called 'Razors and Twigs.'\"","\n","^</p>","\n","^<p>","\n","^The guitar explodes into angular, trebly violence. The synthesizer howls. A drum machine fires armor-piercing beats at high BPM.","\n","^</p>","\n",{"->t->":"yield"},"^<p>","\n","^Sister and Rabies wear sleek mimetic-polycarbon adorned with networked holography chips. The optical patterns on their clothing shift in and out of phase with their background.","\n","^</p>","\n",{"->t->":"yield"},"^<p>","\n","^It wasn't a name I recognized before I arrived. Something new, something that had grown like fungus since the Restoration came to Capital.","\n","^</p>","\n",{"->t->":"yield"},"^<p>","\n","^New microgenres swept through God's country and into the minds of his newest servants at nearly luminal speed. Whole aesthetics could grow overnight then vanish utterly into the kingdom of nostalgia.","\n","^</p>","\n",{"->t->":"yield"},"^<p>","\n","^These women are here to tell us a dirty joke over, drawn from the lineage of all the spectral and youthful DNA created and lost across the Capital.","\n","^</p>","\n",{"->t->":"yield"},"^<p>","\n","^The joke: every popular form, when subjected to enough destabilizing violence, becomes foreign and nearly unlistenable. And so Top 40 tracks become grinding threnodies; ballads become shambolic, amphetamine-fuelled barn-burners; electro hits become plaintive screams and literally burning amplifiers, guitars prepared with metal shims and played with razor-wire baseball bats.","\n","^</p>","\n",{"->t->":"yield"},"^<p>","\n","^At first, I thought their faces were collage of some kind, one of a hundred <em>objets d'art</em> here. Sad, violent girl-faces cut from another image and composited onto a photograph of vomit covering a graffitied wall. Dark eyes, raccoon eyebags, a furious assemblage of semi-digital tattooing.","\n","^</p>","\n",{"->t->":"yield"},"^<p>","\n","^They move with the sinister energy of jungle predators, homeless. Even on stage, their bodies are nearly invisible, abstract patterns and form constants approximating the sagging boards and ancient brickwork bounding the Palace.","\n","^</p>","\n",{"->t->":"yield"},"^<p>","\n","^Sister Cat clicks a pedal with her foot and sings into the microphone, angelic and shrieking, echoing as through a nave, beyond all linguistic coherence.","\n","^</p>","\n","ev","void","/ev","->->",{"#f":1}],chapter_12_halo_of_flies_secondary_stage:['^<stop-sound group="music" name="raw-bit-processor" />',"\n",'^<play-sound group="music" name="razors-and-twigs-diegetic-left" />',"\n",'^<play-sound group="music" name="rage-diegetic-right" />',"\n",'^<play-sound group="music" name="cowardice-live" />',"\n","^<p>","\n",'^Baronette Mantissa plays their hit single "Cowardice." I\'m not exactly sure what "hit" means here, definitely not diamond, probably not even gold.',"\n","^</p>","\n","^<p>","\n","^The kids are eating it up, though, making out, grinding on the floor, throwing beer everywhere, slapping each other about the faces. Maybe I'm the titular coward.","\n","^</p>","\n","^<p>","\n","^Or maybe I'm just getting too old to be a punk anymore.","\n","^</p>","\n","ev","void","/ev","->->",{"#f":1}],chapter_12_halo_of_flies_tertiary_stage:['^<stop-sound group="music" name="raw-bit-processor" />',"\n",'^<play-sound group="music" name="cowardice-diegetic-left" />',"\n",'^<play-sound group="music" name="razors-and-twigs-diegetic-left" />',"\n",'^<play-sound group="music" name="rage-live" />',"\n","^<p>","\n","^Hollywood Baphomets, on first deafening blush, seems an artistic project designed to ascertain how mad one may get, playing a synthesizer, and still receive rapturous dances from the audience.","\n","^</p>","\n","^<p>","\n","^My tablet says this song is called \"Rage.\" It's appropriate. But who even knows? None of these song-detection algorithms can handle a screaming noise-punk show. Could be any of the Baphomets' songs.","\n","^</p>","\n","^<p>","\n",'^"It all sounds the same to me," as the old fogies say.',"\n","^</p>","\n",{"->t->":"yield"},"^<p>","\n","^Wow, did I just admit I'm an old-ass woman now?","\n","^</p>","\n",{"->t->":"yield"},"^<p>","\n","^Better dance like a cool person, carbine jammed alongside my ribs, pain be damned. Then I'll look <em>way</em> younger, right?","\n","^</p>","\n",{"->t->":"yield"},"^<p>","\n","^Why is it no matter which punk show I ever went to, I spent the whole time moping like a woad, thinking about how I <em>looked</em>.","\n","^</p>","\n",{"->t->":"yield"},"^<p>","\n","^Tonight will be different. Mother will ensure that even if the noise rockers don't play ball.","\n","^</p>","\n","ev","void","/ev","->->",{"#f":1}],chapter_12_halo_of_flies_directives_received:["^<p>","\n","^A mothering voice over the radio, so clear over bone-conduction microphone it's like she's standing next to me, sweating and cheering along with us.","\n","^</p>","\n","^<p>","\n","^\"Hannah. The time has come to 'crack open a cold one.' Do as the centurions.\"","\n","^</p>","\n","^<p>","\n","^My hands are dripping with sweat as I reach into my pocket, spacious enough for a pistol, mil-punk olive drab. I fumble with the case.","\n","^</p>","\n",{"->t->":"yield"},'^<update-sound group="music" name="rage-live" volume="0.5" />',"\n","^<p>","\n","^Am I scared? Is it that hot in the Palace, every punk and wastoid dripping all the old drugs out and pouring more in?","\n","^</p>","\n",{"->t->":"yield"},'^<update-sound group="music" name="rage-live" volume="0.45" />',"\n","^<p>","\n","^Is it just the frantically wet punk kids ricocheting around like a hundred pinballs?","\n","^</p>","\n",{"->t->":"yield"},"ev",{"VAR?":"chapter_12_halo_of_flies_band_choice"},"/ev",["du","ev","str","^tiger","/str","==","/ev",{"->":".^.b",c:!0},{b:["pop","\n",'^<play-sound group="music" name="razors-and-twigs-remix-late" />',"\n",{"->":".^.^.^.43"},null]}],["du","ev","str","^baphomet","/str","==","/ev",{"->":".^.b",c:!0},{b:["pop","\n",'^<update-sound group="music" name="rage-live" volume="0.4" />',"\n",{"->":".^.^.^.43"},null]}],"pop","nop","\n","^<p>","\n","^I break the case open and pull the laminated mission directives out.","\n","^</p>","\n",{"->t->":"yield"},'^<update-sound group="music" name="rage-live" volume="0.35" />',"\n","^<p>","\n","^My hands are shaking now. What will be expected of us? What will be demanded?","\n","^</p>","\n",{"->t->":"yield"},'^<update-sound group="music" name="rage-live" volume="0.3" />',"\n",'^<play-sound group="music" name="razors-and-twigs-remix-outro" />',"\n","^<p>","\n","^The card reads:","\n","^</p>","\n","^<blockquote>","\n","^<p>","\n","^GET RID OF FAME","\n","^<br />","\n","^PARASOCIAL HOPE IS A NIGHTMARE THAT HAS BEEN CONSUMING YOU","\n","^<br />","\n","^NOW DEVOUR YOUR AUDIENCE","\n","^</p>","\n","^<p>","\n","^WITH ARDOR EVERLASTING,","\n","^</p>","\n","^<p>M","ev","str","^\\","/str","out","/ev","^F, TA, HB, BM, VK, AC, F, PRSN, IS.</p>","\n","^</blockquote>","\n","ev","void","/ev","->->",{"#f":1}],chapter_12_halo_of_flies_end_of_show:["ev",{"VAR?":"chapter_12_halo_of_flies_band_choice"},"/ev",["du","ev","str","^tiger","/str","==","/ev",{"->":".^.b",c:!0},{b:["pop","\n",'^<stop-sound group="music" name="razors-and-twigs-remix-late" />',"\n",'^<stop-sound group="music" name="razors-and-twigs-remix" />',"\n",'^<stop-sound group="music" name="cowardice-diegetic-right" />',"\n",'^<stop-sound group="music" name="rage-diegetic-right" />',"\n",'^<play-sound group="music" name="rage-live" />',"\n","^<p>","\n","^The band plays out, roaring and incandescent.","\n","^</p>","\n",{"->":".^.^.^.6"},null]}],["du","ev","str","^mantissa","/str","==","/ev",{"->":".^.b",c:!0},{b:["pop","\n",'^<stop-sound group="music" name="cowardice-live" />',"\n",'^<stop-sound group="music" name="razors-and-twigs-diegetic-left" />',"\n",'^<stop-sound group="music" name="rage-diegetic-right" />',"\n",'^<play-sound group="music" name="rage-live" />',"\n","^<p>","\n","^The band plays out, roaring and incandescent.","\n","^</p>","\n",{"->":".^.^.^.6"},null]}],[{"->":".^.b"},{b:["pop","\n",'^<stop-sound group="music" name="cowardice-diegetic-left" />',"\n",'^<stop-sound group="music" name="razors-and-twigs-diegetic-left" />',"\n","^<p>","\n","^Both of the other bands end their violent songs. The Baphomets ring out alone for a minute or three.","\n","^</p>","\n",{"->":".^.^.^.6"},null]}],"nop","\n","^<p>","\n","^The punks dance. The wallflowers grow in shadow. The smell of rotting trash, piss, and beer lords over us all.","\n","^</p>","\n","^<p>","\n","^Just like in the good old days.","\n","^</p>","\n","^<p>","\n","^It's almost time. There will be a signal, and then it will begin.","\n","^</p>","\n","ev","void","/ev","->->",{"#f":1}],chapter_12_halo_of_flies_encore:["ev",{"VAR?":"chapter_12_halo_of_flies_band_choice"},"/ev",["du","ev","str","^tiger","/str","==","/ev",{"->":".^.b",c:!0},{b:["pop","\n",'^<stop-sound group="music" name="cowardice-diegetic-right" />',"\n",'^<stop-sound group="music" name="rage-diegetic-right" />',"\n",'^<play-sound group="music" name="rage-live" volume="0.35" />',"\n",{"->":".^.^.^.6"},null]}],["du","ev","str","^mantissa","/str","==","/ev",{"->":".^.b",c:!0},{b:["pop","\n",'^<stop-sound group="music" name="razors-and-twigs-diegetic-left" />',"\n",'^<stop-sound group="music" name="rage-diegetic-right" />',"\n",'^<stop-sound group="music" name="cowardice-live" />',"\n",'^<play-sound group="music" name="rage-live" volume="0.25" />',"\n",{"->":".^.^.^.6"},null]}],[{"->":".^.b"},{b:["pop","\n",'^<stop-sound group="music" name="cowardice-diegetic-left" />',"\n",'^<stop-sound group="music" name="razors-and-twigs-diegetic-left" />',"\n",'^<update-sound group="music" name="rage-live" volume="0.25" />',"\n",{"->":".^.^.^.6"},null]}],"nop","\n","^<p>","\n","^All of the bands but one end their set, and begin to pack up their instruments.","\n","^</p>","\n",{"->t->":"yield"},"^<p>","\n","^Guitars go in cases.","\n","^</p>","\n","^<p>","\n","^Drums are folded and stacked.","\n","^</p>","\n","^<p>","\n","^Synthesizers are caressed, placed in soft coverings, and held firmly to the breast.","\n","^</p>","\n","^<p>","\n","^The gnashing and wailing of the crowd, for encore, for more sound-violence, all ignored.","\n","^</p>","\n","^<p>","\n","^Still the crowd squalls.","\n","^</p>","\n","^<p>","\n","^Rather than walking behind the curtain or out the doors, each band moves slowly and heavily over to the tertiary stage, way back in the depths of the Palace, where Hollywood Baphomets is just finishing their terrible synthesized blitzkriegs.","\n","^</p>","\n",{"->t->":"yield"},'^<stop-sound group="music" name="rage-live" />',"\n",'^<play-sound group="music" name="threnody-for-the-fans" />',"\n","^<p>","\n","^Then the Baphomets stop playing, lay the guitar against amp, let the noise build and recombine. All eight bands set up all their gear on the same stage and begin to play at once.","\n","^</p>","\n","^<p>","\n","^A monolithic symphony of distortion and atonality.","\n","^</p>","\n","^<p>","\n","^Polyrhythmic and heteroglossic.","\n","^</p>","\n","^<p>","\n","^Deafening and insistent, loving and terrible.","\n","^</p>","\n",{"->t->":"yield"},"^<p>","\n","^Intense strobes flash.","\n","^</p>","\n","^<p>","\n","^All the children begin the deathdance, skanking, pogoing, moshing, slam-dancing, proceeding in turn, step by historical step.","\n","^</p>","\n","^<p>","\n","^Several larger boys run around like jousters, knocking each other off their feet and tackling one another to the ground.","\n","^</p>","\n",{"->t->":"yield"},"^<p>","\n","^Enormous pyrotechnic displays erupt behind the bands, for the first time all night.","\n","^</p>","\n","^<p>","\n","^Burning tongues lick at the ceiling.","\n","^</p>","\n","^<p>","\n","^Flames race along the old insulation-stuffed ceilings, falling among the artful detritus of the warehouse.","\n","^</p>","\n",{"->t->":"yield"},"^<p>","\n","^The groove elongates and begins to collapse into itself.","\n","^</p>","\n","^<p>","\n","^The drummers lose the beat and shift to double time.","\n","^</p>","\n",{"->t->":"yield"},"^<p>","\n","^Urethane, polyethylene, extension cords, wrappers and old posters, tapestries, palimpsests of stickers, sheet-metal, hot magnesium rain, fevered young eyes: all glow.","\n","^</p>","\n","^<p>","\n","^Satya rewinds towards Kali.","\n","^</p>","\n",{"->t->":"yield"},"^<p>","\n","^The highest tone plays, like a rusty swing in the wind. This is the cue to begin.","\n","^</p>","\n",{"->t->":"yield"},"^<p>","\n","^And begin we do, with one, two, three sharp bangs far louder and harder than any amplifier could ever manage.","\n","^</p>","\n","^<p>","\n","^Several screams cut through the sound. An arm and a leg fly through the air like beach balls at an electro rave. It could be a Perfect, it could be a fan.","\n","^</p>","\n","^<p>","\n","^All souls are merely ours now.","\n","^</p>","\n","^<p>","\n","^The rifles open up, and the gunshots become an instrument unto themselves. It's too loud for screams or prayers to be heard. Another two suicide vests go off and a portion of the crowd goes flying in all directions.","\n","^</p>","\n","^<p>","\n","^The music carries on, two drums, one guitar, one synthesizer barely keeping up on harmony and bass, three-fingered and one-handed. The instruments drop out one by one until only one drummer remains.","\n","^</p>","\n",{"->t->":"yield"},"^<p>","\n","^The room is full of smoke.","\n","^</p>","\n","^<p>","\n","^The Operating Group, labors now complete, toss aside weapons, costumes, wiping off blood and soot and leaving all behind. We pour out into the night, dispersing within several klicks, hiding out in alleys and safe houses and caf\xe9s. Each of us watches the work's remainder through the eyes of those who must die, all fully wired for picture and sound, down to the death.","\n","^</p>","\n",{"->t->":"yield"},'^<stop-sound group="music" name="threnody-for-the-fans" />',"\n",'^<play-sound group="music" name="too-much-sunlight" />',"\n","^<p>","\n","^Those who would still end some lives by bullets and grenades rather than smoke pull on masks and infrared goggles. Bullets spin around every angle of the room like a maypole in construction, whirling around and under and over. Many fall to friendly fire. But every bullet is friendly now, every grenade transformative. All the last gasps of toxic and plastic air are the last pains of those who shall never ache again. The eschaton will be inherited by those who cry out first. They will wait there us.","\n","^</p>","\n","^<p>","\n","^The fire's spit is like darkness, growing. Structural elements, beams and girders, the bones holding it all together, they begin to moan and roar.","\n","^</p>","\n","^<p>","\n","^Ammo runs dry. There ceases to be oxygen to filter in a room which is now nearly all fire and its leavings. The Perfect who can still move and think each trigger their belts. All detonate.","\n","^</p>","\n","^<p>","\n","^Everyone trips over themselves, onto each other, into the vast thicket of things, towards the exits now packed like sardines in a crushed tin can. Several videographers stand outside the doors, further blocking progress, training their gaze on those who are trapped, and will certainly burn.","\n","^</p>","\n","^<p>","\n","^The students and the artists and the tourists and the changelings and the crusties are torn to shreds and gasping for air, running in circles in the blinding smoke.","\n","^</p>","\n",{"->t->":"yield"},"^<p>","\n","^The best of us die tonight, on all sides and in every ersatz room of the warehouse.","\n","^</p>","\n","^<p>","\n","^The roof falls. The Palace has become a temple of death, razed to the ground.","\n","^</p>","\n","^<p>","\n","^The signal cuts to black.","\n","^</p>","\n","ev","void","/ev","->->",{"#f":1}],yield:[["ev","str","^\u25fc","/str","/ev",{"*":".^.c-0",flg:4},{"c-0":["\n",{"->":".^.^.g-0"},{"#f":5}],"g-0":["ev","void","/ev","->->",{"#f":5}]}],{"#f":1}],done:[{"temp=":"out_var"},[["ev",{"VAR?":"out_var"},"/ev",{"->":".^.b",c:!0},{b:["\n","ev",{"VAR?":"out_var"},"/ev",{"VAR=":"XLR8R_OUT_PASSAGE",re:!0},{"->":"done.1.1"},null]}],"nop","\n","ev","str","^\u25fc","/str","/ev",{"*":".^.c-0",flg:20},{"c-0":["\n",{"->":".^.^.g-0"},{"#f":5}],"g-0":['^<stop-sound group="music" name="too-much-sunlight" />',"\n","done",{"#f":5}]}],{"#f":1}],"global decl":["ev","str","^XLR8R_PREVIOUS_VALUE","/str",{"VAR=":"DEBUG"},"str","^chapter-13","/str",{"VAR=":"XLR8R_OUT_PASSAGE"},"str","^","/str",{"VAR=":"chapter_12_halo_of_flies_band_choice"},"str","^","/str",{"VAR=":"chapter_12_halo_of_flies_name_choice"},"/ev","end",null],"#f":1}],listDefs:{}},text:'VAR DEBUG = "XLR8R_PREVIOUS_VALUE"\r\n\r\nVAR XLR8R_OUT_PASSAGE = "chapter-13"\r\n\r\n\r\nVAR chapter_12_halo_of_flies_band_choice = ""\r\nVAR chapter_12_halo_of_flies_name_choice = ""\r\n\r\n\r\n-> chapter_12_halo_of_flies_start ->\r\n\r\n-> yield ->\r\n\r\n-> chapter_12_halo_of_flies_directives_received ->\r\n\r\n-> yield ->\r\n\r\n-> chapter_12_halo_of_flies_end_of_show ->\r\n\r\n-> yield ->\r\n\r\n-> chapter_12_halo_of_flies_encore ->\r\n\r\n-> done("")\r\n\r\n\r\n=== chapter_12_halo_of_flies_start ===\r\n<play-sound group="music" name="boardroom-daydream" />\r\n\r\n<play-sound group="music" name="raw-bit-processor" />\r\n\r\n<h5><time>2301.06.14:1730</time></h5>\r\n\r\n<p>\r\nEvening. The sun just beginning to creep under the horizon. All the smog is bright as the sun stares us down, straight on.\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n-> yield ->\r\n\r\n<p>\r\nThe Palace is alive, though. Eight bands, one night, four hours of extreme noise played by mad anarcho-punks. We\'re <em>very</em> fashionably late, and the openers are already done. Show probably opened late, too.\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<p>\r\nThe flier is stuck to all the walls outside, and in the lobby.\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n    <li>Tiger Actual</li>\r\n    <li>Hollywood Baphomets </li>\r\n    <li>Baronette Mantissa</li>\r\n    <li>Violence Kings</li>\r\n    <li>ADAM Contingent</li>\r\n    <li>FUBAR</li>\r\n    <li>The People\'s Revolutionary Society of Noise</li>\r\n    <li>Interrupt Signal</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>\r\nThe warehouse has three stages, one primary, two secondary.\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n-> yield ->\r\n\r\n<stop-sound group="music" name="boardroom-daydream" />\r\n\r\n<update-sound group="music" name="raw-bit-processor" volume="0.35" />\r\n\r\n<p>\r\nTiger Actual, FUBAR, and the PRSN are playing the primary stage.\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<p>\r\nThe Violence Kings, ADAM Contingent (less its recent frontman, suspected on the matrix of liking young girls a bit too much; they executed his termination in classic punk style), and Baron Mantissa are on one secondary stage.\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<p>\r\nHollywood Baphomets and Interrupt Signal are on the other.\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n-> yield ->\r\n\r\n<p>\r\nThe crowd is beginning to pack in. All colors and genders, sovereign in the postdiluvian night, mostly very young. They have fierce eyes and impossibly wide smiles, laughs barking in the dark structure now growing opaque through smoke machines and vaporized psychoactives.\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<p>\r\nI am in the corner, watching the headcount grow. Lystra and Lefteris are off scoping the exits. I\'m catching the tunes, and they\'ll go to whichever stages I don\'t.\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<p>\r\nA carbine is digging into my ribs under an elaborate and skinless anarcho-death getup. The rest of the operating group is in similar vestments, scattered near the exits and hallways.\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<p>\r\nA punk girl needs a hardcore name, of course.\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n* (andrea) Andrea "Methedrine" Eldridge.\r\n    ~ chapter_12_halo_of_flies_name_choice = "Andrea \\"Methedrine\\" Eldridge"\r\n* (justina) Justina Putrescence.\r\n    ~ chapter_12_halo_of_flies_name_choice = "Justina Putrescence"\r\n* Plural Melanie And Their Scumfucs.\r\n    ~ chapter_12_halo_of_flies_name_choice = "Plural Melanie And Their Scumfucs"\r\n-\r\n\r\n<p>\r\nHardest name in the entire damn Palace. Nobody fucks with <>{\r\n    - andrea:\r\n        Methedrine Eldridge.\r\n    - justina:\r\n        Justina Putrescence.\r\n    - else:\r\n        <>Plural Melanie. Or their innumerably vicious Scumfucs.\r\n}\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n* I move to the primary stage.\r\n    ~ chapter_12_halo_of_flies_band_choice = "tiger"\r\n\r\n    -> chapter_12_halo_of_flies_primary_stage ->\r\n* I\'ll watch the secondary stage.\r\n    ~ chapter_12_halo_of_flies_band_choice = "mantissa"\r\n\r\n    -> chapter_12_halo_of_flies_secondary_stage ->\r\n* I\'m going to the tertiary stage.\r\n    ~ chapter_12_halo_of_flies_band_choice = "baphomet"\r\n\r\n    -> chapter_12_halo_of_flies_tertiary_stage ->\r\n-\r\n\r\n->->\r\n\r\n\r\n=== chapter_12_halo_of_flies_primary_stage ===\r\n<p>\r\nTiger Actual is opening. A few kids in a cluster to my right are looking the band up on their devices and sharing what they find. Two women. Sister Cat and Rabies Sonderlust. Synthesizers. Noise. Dancing.\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n-> yield ->\r\n\r\n<stop-sound group="music" name="raw-bit-processor" />\r\n\r\n<play-sound group="music" name="cowardice-diegetic-right" />\r\n\r\n<play-sound group="music" name="rage-diegetic-right" />\r\n\r\n<play-sound group="music" name="razors-and-twigs-remix" />\r\n\r\n<p>\r\nThe duo steps up to the stage, guitar and synthesizer in hand, lips poised above microphones. Rabies speaks: "This is a song called \'Razors and Twigs.\'"\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<p>\r\nThe guitar explodes into angular, trebly violence. The synthesizer howls. A drum machine fires armor-piercing beats at high BPM.\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n-> yield ->\r\n\r\n<p>\r\nSister and Rabies wear sleek mimetic-polycarbon adorned with networked holography chips. The optical patterns on their clothing shift in and out of phase with their background.\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n-> yield ->\r\n\r\n<p>\r\nIt wasn\'t a name I recognized before I arrived. Something new, something that had grown like fungus since the Restoration came to Capital.\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n-> yield ->\r\n\r\n<p>\r\nNew microgenres swept through God\'s country and into the minds of his newest servants at nearly luminal speed. Whole aesthetics could grow overnight then vanish utterly into the kingdom of nostalgia.\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n-> yield ->\r\n\r\n<p>\r\nThese women are here to tell us a dirty joke over, drawn from the lineage of all the spectral and youthful DNA created and lost across the Capital.\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n-> yield ->\r\n\r\n<p>\r\nThe joke: every popular form, when subjected to enough destabilizing violence, becomes foreign and nearly unlistenable. And so Top 40 tracks become grinding threnodies; ballads become shambolic, amphetamine-fuelled barn-burners; electro hits become plaintive screams and literally burning amplifiers, guitars prepared with metal shims and played with razor-wire baseball bats.\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n-> yield ->\r\n\r\n<p>\r\nAt first, I thought their faces were collage of some kind, one of a hundred <em>objets d\'art</em> here. Sad, violent girl-faces cut from another image and composited onto a photograph of vomit covering a graffitied wall. Dark eyes, raccoon eyebags, a furious assemblage of semi-digital tattooing.\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n-> yield ->\r\n\r\n<p>\r\nThey move with the sinister energy of jungle predators, homeless. Even on stage, their bodies are nearly invisible, abstract patterns and form constants approximating the sagging boards and ancient brickwork bounding the Palace.\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n-> yield ->\r\n\r\n<p>\r\nSister Cat clicks a pedal with her foot and sings into the microphone, angelic and shrieking, echoing as through a nave, beyond all linguistic coherence.\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n->->\r\n\r\n\r\n=== chapter_12_halo_of_flies_secondary_stage ===\r\n<stop-sound group="music" name="raw-bit-processor" />\r\n\r\n<play-sound group="music" name="razors-and-twigs-diegetic-left" />\r\n\r\n<play-sound group="music" name="rage-diegetic-right" />\r\n\r\n<play-sound group="music" name="cowardice-live" />\r\n\r\n<p>\r\nBaronette Mantissa plays their hit single "Cowardice." I\'m not exactly sure what "hit" means here, definitely not diamond, probably not even gold.\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<p>\r\nThe kids are eating it up, though, making out, grinding on the floor, throwing beer everywhere, slapping each other about the faces. Maybe I\'m the titular coward.\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<p>\r\nOr maybe I\'m just getting too old to be a punk anymore.\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n->->\r\n\r\n\r\n=== chapter_12_halo_of_flies_tertiary_stage ===\r\n<stop-sound group="music" name="raw-bit-processor" />\r\n\r\n<play-sound group="music" name="cowardice-diegetic-left" />\r\n\r\n<play-sound group="music" name="razors-and-twigs-diegetic-left" />\r\n\r\n<play-sound group="music" name="rage-live" />\r\n\r\n<p>\r\nHollywood Baphomets, on first deafening blush, seems an artistic project designed to ascertain how mad one may get, playing a synthesizer, and still receive rapturous dances from the audience.\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<p>\r\nMy tablet says this song is called "Rage." It\'s appropriate. But who even knows? None of these song-detection algorithms can handle a screaming noise-punk show. Could be any of the Baphomets\' songs.\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<p>\r\n"It all sounds the same to me," as the old fogies say.\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n-> yield ->\r\n\r\n<p>\r\nWow, did I just admit I\'m an old-ass woman now?\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n-> yield ->\r\n\r\n<p>\r\nBetter dance like a cool person, carbine jammed alongside my ribs, pain be damned. Then I\'ll look <em>way</em> younger, right?\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n-> yield ->\r\n\r\n<p>\r\nWhy is it no matter which punk show I ever went to, I spent the whole time moping like a woad, thinking about how I <em>looked</em>.\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n-> yield ->\r\n\r\n<p>\r\nTonight will be different. Mother will ensure that even if the noise rockers don\'t play ball.\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n->->\r\n\r\n\r\n=== chapter_12_halo_of_flies_directives_received ===\r\n<p>\r\nA mothering voice over the radio, so clear over bone-conduction microphone it\'s like she\'s standing next to me, sweating and cheering along with us.\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<p>\r\n"Hannah. The time has come to \'crack open a cold one.\' Do as the centurions."\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<p>\r\nMy hands are dripping with sweat as I reach into my pocket, spacious enough for a pistol, mil-punk olive drab. I fumble with the case.\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n-> yield ->\r\n\r\n<update-sound group="music" name="rage-live" volume="0.5" />\r\n\r\n<p>\r\nAm I scared? Is it that hot in the Palace, every punk and wastoid dripping all the old drugs out and pouring more in?\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n-> yield ->\r\n\r\n<update-sound group="music" name="rage-live" volume="0.45" />\r\n\r\n<p>\r\nIs it just the frantically wet punk kids ricocheting around like a hundred pinballs?\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n-> yield ->\r\n\r\n{chapter_12_halo_of_flies_band_choice:\r\n    - "tiger":\r\n        <play-sound group="music" name="razors-and-twigs-remix-late" />\r\n    - "baphomet":\r\n        <update-sound group="music" name="rage-live" volume="0.4" />\r\n}\r\n\r\n<p>\r\nI break the case open and pull the laminated mission directives out.\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n-> yield ->\r\n\r\n<update-sound group="music" name="rage-live" volume="0.35" />\r\n\r\n<p>\r\nMy hands are shaking now. What will be expected of us? What will be demanded?\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n-> yield ->\r\n\r\n<update-sound group="music" name="rage-live" volume="0.3" />\r\n\r\n<play-sound group="music" name="razors-and-twigs-remix-outro" />\r\n\r\n<p>\r\nThe card reads:\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<blockquote>\r\n<p>\r\nGET RID OF FAME\r\n<br />\r\nPARASOCIAL HOPE IS A NIGHTMARE THAT HAS BEEN CONSUMING YOU\r\n<br />\r\nNOW DEVOUR YOUR AUDIENCE\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<p>\r\nWITH ARDOR EVERLASTING,\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<p>M{"\\\\"}F, TA, HB, BM, VK, AC, F, PRSN, IS.</p>\r\n</blockquote>\r\n\r\n->->\r\n\r\n\r\n=== chapter_12_halo_of_flies_end_of_show ===\r\n{chapter_12_halo_of_flies_band_choice:\r\n    - "tiger":\r\n        <stop-sound group="music" name="razors-and-twigs-remix-late" />\r\n\r\n        <stop-sound group="music" name="razors-and-twigs-remix" />\r\n\r\n        <stop-sound group="music" name="cowardice-diegetic-right" />\r\n\r\n        <stop-sound group="music" name="rage-diegetic-right" />\r\n\r\n        <play-sound group="music" name="rage-live" />\r\n\r\n        <p>\r\n        The band plays out, roaring and incandescent.\r\n        </p>\r\n    - "mantissa":\r\n        <stop-sound group="music" name="cowardice-live" />\r\n\r\n        <stop-sound group="music" name="razors-and-twigs-diegetic-left" />\r\n\r\n        <stop-sound group="music" name="rage-diegetic-right" />\r\n\r\n        <play-sound group="music" name="rage-live" />\r\n\r\n        <p>\r\n        The band plays out, roaring and incandescent.\r\n        </p>\r\n    - else:\r\n        <stop-sound group="music" name="cowardice-diegetic-left" />\r\n\r\n        <stop-sound group="music" name="razors-and-twigs-diegetic-left" />\r\n\r\n        <p>\r\n        Both of the other bands end their violent songs. The Baphomets ring out alone for a minute or three.\r\n        </p>\r\n}\r\n\r\n<p>\r\nThe punks dance. The wallflowers grow in shadow. The smell of rotting trash, piss, and beer lords over us all. \r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<p>\r\nJust like in the good old days.\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<p>\r\nIt\'s almost time. There will be a signal, and then it will begin.\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n->->\r\n\r\n=== chapter_12_halo_of_flies_encore ===\r\n{chapter_12_halo_of_flies_band_choice:\r\n    - "tiger":\r\n        <stop-sound group="music" name="cowardice-diegetic-right" />\r\n\r\n        <stop-sound group="music" name="rage-diegetic-right" />\r\n\r\n        <play-sound group="music" name="rage-live" volume="0.35" />\r\n    - "mantissa":\r\n        <stop-sound group="music" name="razors-and-twigs-diegetic-left" />\r\n\r\n        <stop-sound group="music" name="rage-diegetic-right" />\r\n\r\n        <stop-sound group="music" name="cowardice-live" />\r\n\r\n        <play-sound group="music" name="rage-live" volume="0.25" />\r\n    - else:\r\n        <stop-sound group="music" name="cowardice-diegetic-left" />\r\n\r\n        <stop-sound group="music" name="razors-and-twigs-diegetic-left" />\r\n\r\n        <update-sound group="music" name="rage-live" volume="0.25" />\r\n}\r\n\r\n<p>\r\nAll of the bands but one end their set, and begin to pack up their instruments.\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n-> yield ->\r\n\r\n<p>\r\nGuitars go in cases.\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<p>\r\nDrums are folded and stacked.\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<p>\r\nSynthesizers are caressed, placed in soft coverings, and held firmly to the breast.\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<p>\r\nThe gnashing and wailing of the crowd, for encore, for more sound-violence, all ignored.\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<p>\r\nStill the crowd squalls.\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<p>\r\nRather than walking behind the curtain or out the doors, each band moves slowly and heavily over to the tertiary stage, way back in the depths of the Palace, where Hollywood Baphomets is just finishing their terrible synthesized blitzkriegs.\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n-> yield ->\r\n\r\n<stop-sound group="music" name="rage-live" />\r\n\r\n<play-sound group="music" name="threnody-for-the-fans" />\r\n\r\n<p>\r\nThen the Baphomets stop playing, lay the guitar against amp, let the noise build and recombine. All eight bands set up all their gear on the same stage and begin to play at once.\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<p>\r\nA monolithic symphony of distortion and atonality.\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<p>\r\nPolyrhythmic and heteroglossic.\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<p>\r\nDeafening and insistent, loving and terrible.\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n-> yield ->\r\n\r\n<p>\r\nIntense strobes flash.\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<p>\r\nAll the children begin the deathdance, skanking, pogoing, moshing, slam-dancing, proceeding in turn, step by historical step.\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<p>\r\nSeveral larger boys run around like jousters, knocking each other off their feet and tackling one another to the ground.\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n-> yield ->\r\n\r\n<p>\r\nEnormous pyrotechnic displays erupt behind the bands, for the first time all night.\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<p>\r\nBurning tongues lick at the ceiling.\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<p>\r\nFlames race along the old insulation-stuffed ceilings, falling among the artful detritus of the warehouse.\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n-> yield ->\r\n\r\n<p>\r\nThe groove elongates and begins to collapse into itself.\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<p>\r\nThe drummers lose the beat and shift to double time.\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n-> yield ->\r\n\r\n<p>\r\nUrethane, polyethylene, extension cords, wrappers and old posters, tapestries, palimpsests of stickers, sheet-metal, hot magnesium rain, fevered young eyes: all glow.\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<p>\r\nSatya rewinds towards Kali.\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n-> yield ->\r\n\r\n<p>\r\nThe highest tone plays, like a rusty swing in the wind. This is the cue to begin.\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n-> yield ->\r\n\r\n<p>\r\nAnd begin we do, with one, two, three sharp bangs far louder and harder than any amplifier could ever manage.\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<p>\r\nSeveral screams cut through the sound. An arm and a leg fly through the air like beach balls at an electro rave. It could be a Perfect, it could be a fan.\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<p>\r\nAll souls are merely ours now.\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<p>\r\nThe rifles open up, and the gunshots become an instrument unto themselves. It\'s too loud for screams or prayers to be heard. Another two suicide vests go off and a portion of the crowd goes flying in all directions.\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<p>\r\nThe music carries on, two drums, one guitar, one synthesizer barely keeping up on harmony and bass, three-fingered and one-handed. The instruments drop out one by one until only one drummer remains.\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n-> yield ->\r\n\r\n<p>\r\nThe room is full of smoke.\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<p>\r\nThe Operating Group, labors now complete, toss aside weapons, costumes, wiping off blood and soot and leaving all behind. We pour out into the night, dispersing within several klicks, hiding out in alleys and safe houses and caf\xe9s. Each of us watches the work\'s remainder through the eyes of those who must die, all fully wired for picture and sound, down to the death.\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n-> yield ->\r\n\r\n<stop-sound group="music" name="threnody-for-the-fans" />\r\n\r\n<play-sound group="music" name="too-much-sunlight" />\r\n\r\n<p>\r\nThose who would still end some lives by bullets and grenades rather than smoke pull on masks and infrared goggles. Bullets spin around every angle of the room like a maypole in construction, whirling around and under and over. Many fall to friendly fire. But every bullet is friendly now, every grenade transformative. All the last gasps of toxic and plastic air are the last pains of those who shall never ache again. The eschaton will be inherited by those who cry out first. They will wait there us.\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<p>\r\nThe fire\'s spit is like darkness, growing. Structural elements, beams and girders, the bones holding it all together, they begin to moan and roar.\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<p>\r\nAmmo runs dry. There ceases to be oxygen to filter in a room which is now nearly all fire and its leavings. The Perfect who can still move and think each trigger their belts. All detonate.\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<p>\r\nEveryone trips over themselves, onto each other, into the vast thicket of things, towards the exits now packed like sardines in a crushed tin can. Several videographers stand outside the doors, further blocking progress, training their gaze on those who are trapped, and will certainly burn.\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<p>\r\nThe students and the artists and the tourists and the changelings and the crusties are torn to shreds and gasping for air, running in circles in the blinding smoke.\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n\r\n-> yield ->\r\n\r\n<p>\r\nThe best of us die tonight, on all sides and in every ersatz room of the warehouse.\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<p>\r\nThe roof falls. The Palace has become a temple of death, razed to the ground.\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<p>\r\nThe signal cuts to black.\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n->->\r\n\r\n\r\n=== yield ===\r\n+ [\u25fc]\r\n-\r\n\r\n->->\r\n\r\n\r\n=== done(out_var) ===\r\n{\r\n    - out_var:\r\n        ~ XLR8R_OUT_PASSAGE = out_var\r\n}\r\n\r\n* [\u25fc]\r\n-\r\n\r\n<stop-sound group="music" name="too-much-sunlight" />\r\n\r\n-> DONE'}}}]);